messages.content: ComfyUI_ID_Animator is a custom node for ComfyUI that integrates the ID_Animator model for generating animated images and videos.
Where can I find the ID_Animator model?
The ID_Animator model can be found at the following link: [ID_Animator](https://github.com/ID-Animator/ID-Animator).
What are some other custom nodes mentioned for ComfyUI?

Some other custom nodes mentioned for ComfyUI include ComfyUI_ParlerTTS, ComfyUI_Llama3_8B, ComfyUI_HiDiffusion_Pro, ComfyUI_StoryDiffusion, ComfyUI_Pops, ComfyUI_StableAudio_Open, ComfyUI_ChatGLM_API, ComfyUI_CustomNet, ComfyUI_Pipeline_Tool, ComfyUI_Pic2Story, and ComfyUI_PBR_Maker.
What was fixed in the June 15, 2024 update of ComfyUI_ID_Animator?

In the June 15, 2024 update of ComfyUI_ID_Animator, the issue of animateddiff having a maximum frame rate of 32 was fixed. Conditional control for face_lora and lora_adapter was also added, and support for diffuser versions 0.28.0 and above was included.
To install ComfyUI_ID_Animator, use the following command: `git https://github.com/smthemex/ComfyUI_ID_Animator.git`.
What should I do if a module is missing when installing ComfyUI_ID_Animator?
If a module is missing during the installation of ComfyUI_ID_Animator, open the 'if miss module check this requirements.txt' file and install the missing module separately.
Where can I find examples of ComfyUI_ID_Animator in action?
You can find a demo GIF of ComfyUI_ID_Animator in action at the following link: https://github.com/smthemex/ComfyUI_ID_Animator/blob/main/demo/ComfyUI_ID_Animator.gif.
Who are the creators of ID_Animator?
The creators of ID_Animator are Xuanhua He, Quande Liu, and Shengju Qian. Their contact emails are hexuanhua@mail.ustc.edu.cn, qdliu0226@gmail.com, and thesouthfrog@gmail.com, respectively.
